BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:music-worx-incubator-hamburg-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260613T225027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260617
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260618
SUMMARY:Deadline: Music WorX: Music-Tech Incubator 2026 (Hamburg)
DESCRIPTION:Music WorX is the music-technology incubator run by Hamburg Kre
 ativ Gesellschaft for early-stage teams building products at the intersect
 ion of music and technology (creation tools\, interactive media\, streamin
 g and monetisation\, AI for music\, instruments and audio gear). Selected 
 teams receive a EUR 3\,200 development budget for support services plus a 
 EUR 1\,500 per month living allowance over the 3-month programme\, mentori
 ng from a European music-tech network\, and the chance to win a EUR 1\,000
  audience prize and a EUR 2\,500 jury prize at demo day. The incubator tak
 es no equity. Open to European founders and founding teams (teams of at le
 ast two recommended\, solo founders welcome)\; no formal company formation
  is required to apply. The programme runs roughly September to December 20
 26. Application deadline: 17 June 2026. Apply via the Airtable form linked
  from the official programme page.\n\nOrganisation: Hamburg Kreativ Gesell
 schaft (Kreativ Gesellschaft)\nLocation: Hamburg\, Germany. Open to Europe
 an founders and founding teams\; Hamburg-anchored program with a European 
 mentor network.\nAward: EUR 3\,200 development budget per team plus a EUR 
 1\,500 per month living allowance across the 3-month programme. End-of-pro
 gramme prizes: EUR 1\,000 audience award and EUR 2\,500 jury award. No equ
 ity is taken. No application fee.\nDuration: 3-month programme\, roughly e
 arly September to early December 2026.\n\nMore: https://kreativgesellschaf
 t.org/en/innovation-inkubatoren/inkubatoren/music-worx/
URL:https://kreativgesellschaft.org/en/innovation-inkubatoren/inkubatoren/m
 usic-worx/
LOCATION:Hamburg\, Germany. Open to European founders and founding teams\; 
 Hamburg-anchored program with a European mentor network.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eic-accelerator-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260613T225027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260708
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260709
SUMMARY:Deadline: EIC Accelerator 2026 (European Innovation Council)
DESCRIPTION:The EIC Accelerator funds high-risk\, high-impact deep-tech SME
 s and start-ups to develop and scale breakthrough innovations. It offers a
  grant of up to EUR 2.5 million (a non-dilutive lump sum) for innovation a
 ctivities\, and can combine this with an equity investment of EUR 1-10 mil
 lion through the EIC Fund (blended finance)\, or provide investment only. 
 The Step 1 short application can be submitted at any time\; full (Step 2) 
 applications are evaluated at fixed cut-offs. The next 2026 cut-offs are 8
  July\, 2 September and 4 November 2026 (all 17:00 Brussels time). Eligibl
 e applicants are for-profit SMEs and start-ups (fewer than 250 employees\,
  turnover up to EUR 50M or balance sheet up to EUR 43M) established in an 
 EU Member State or Horizon Europe Associated Country\; small mid-caps up t
 o 499 employees are eligible for investment-only support. Apply via the EU
  Funding and Tenders portal (topic HORIZON-EIC-2026-ACCELERATOR-01).\n\nOr
 ganisation: European Innovation Council (European Commission)\nLocation: E
 U Member States and Horizon Europe Associated Countries. Single-company ap
 plicants\; third-country applicants must relocate before the full-applicat
 ion stage.\nAward: Grant up to EUR 2.5 million (non-dilutive lump sum) for
  innovation activities\, plus optional equity investment of EUR 1-10 milli
 on via the EIC Fund. Options: grant-only\, blended finance\, or investment
 -only. No application fee.\nDuration: Project-based\; supports development
  and scale-up at TRL 5/6 to 8.\n\nMore: https://eic.ec.europa.eu/eic-fundi
 ng-opportunities/eic-accelerator_en
URL:https://eic.ec.europa.eu/eic-funding-opportunities/eic-accelerator_en
LOCATION:EU Member States and Horizon Europe Associated Countries. Single-c
 ompany applicants\; third-country applicants must relocate before the full
 -application stage.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eurostars-call-11-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260613T225027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260910
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260911
SUMMARY:Deadline: Eurostars Call 11 2026 (Eureka / Eurostars-3)
DESCRIPTION:Eurostars (part of the Eureka network\, the Eurostars-3 program
 me co-funded by Horizon Europe) supports collaborative international R&D p
 rojects led by innovative SMEs. Each country funds its own participants\, 
 so amounts vary\; for the Dutch share\, RVO funds up to EUR 500\,000 per p
 roject at a 50 percent reimbursement rate on eligible R&D costs. Projects 
 require an international consortium of at least two independent organisati
 ons from at least two Eurostars countries\, led by an innovative SME\, wit
 h the SME budget at least 50 percent of the total and no single participan
 t exceeding 70 percent. Projects must run no longer than 36 months and be 
 civil (non-defence) in purpose. Call 11 opens 9 July 2026 and closes 10 Se
 ptember 2026\, 14:00 CEST. No application fee. Submit via the Eureka proje
 ct platform (myeurekaproject.org)\; Dutch national information at RVO.\n\n
 Organisation: Eureka / Eurostars-3 (Dutch participation via RVO)\nLocation
 : International consortia from at least two Eurostars countries\, led by a
 n innovative SME. Dutch funding administered by RVO.\nAward: Co-funds coll
 aborative international R&D\; national funding varies by country. For the 
 Dutch project share: up to EUR 500\,000 per project at 50 percent reimburs
 ement of eligible R&D costs. No application fee.\nDuration: Projects up to
  36 months.\n\nMore: https://www.eurekanetwork.org/programmes-and-calls/eu
 rostars/eurostars-call-for-projects-september-2026/
URL:https://www.eurekanetwork.org/programmes-and-calls/eurostars/eurostars-
 call-for-projects-september-2026/
LOCATION:International consortia from at least two Eurostars countries\, le
 d by an innovative SME. Dutch funding administered by RVO.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prototype-fund-class-03-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260613T225027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261130
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261201
SUMMARY:Deadline: Prototype Fund Class 03 (Open-Source Software)
DESCRIPTION:Prototype Fund supports the development of socially relevant op
 en-source software\, offering low-threshold funding and coaching to indivi
 dual developers and small teams. ELIGIBILITY: individual developers or tea
 ms of up to four\; funded members must reside in the EU and the lead entit
 y must be based in Germany. Application window 1 October to 30 November 20
 26. Apply via the Prototype Fund application page.\n\nOrganisation: Protot
 ype Fund (Open Knowledge Foundation Germany)\nLocation: Germany / EU (lead
  must be based in Germany\; funded members must reside in the EU)\nAward: 
 Up to EUR 95\,000 over 6 months\, or up to EUR 158\,000 over 10 months\, p
 lus coaching. No application fee.\nDuration: 6 or 10 months\n\nMore: https
 ://www.prototypefund.de/en/application
URL:https://www.prototypefund.de/en/application
LOCATION:Germany / EU (lead must be based in Germany\; funded members must 
 reside in the EU)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:coe-democracy-hackathon-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260613T225027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260605
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260606
SUMMARY:Deadline: Council of Europe: New Democratic Pact for Europe Democra
 cy Hackathon 2026 (Strasbourg)
DESCRIPTION:Council of Europe civic-tech hackathon to combat online hate sp
 eech and develop tech solutions for democracy\, run alongside No Hate Spee
 ch Week and backed by a Microsoft prize pool. Four challenge tracks cover 
 privacy-preserving hate speech detection\, identifying coordinated inauthe
 ntic behaviour\, gender-based violence reporting systems\, and innovative 
 social transformation approaches. ELIGIBILITY: pre-formed multidisciplinar
 y teams of 3-4 (typically a technologist/developer\, a democracy or policy
  expert\, and a designer or UX innovator)\; residents of the 46 Council of
  Europe member states\; coding experience is not required for every team m
 ember. FORMAT: four online warm-up sessions\, then a three-day in-person f
 inale at the Palais de l'Europe\, Strasbourg\, 17-19 June 2026.\n\nOrganis
 ation: Council of Europe (under the Monaco Presidency of the Committee of 
 Ministers)\, in partnership with No Hate Speech Week and Microsoft\nLocati
 on: Palais de l'Europe\, Strasbourg\, France (hybrid: four online warm-up 
 sessions leading to a three-day in-person finale)\nAward: EUR 50\,000 Micr
 osoft-funded prize pool distributed among winning teams. Travel and accomm
 odation covered for the 20 selected finalist teams. No application fee.\nD
 uration: Online warm-up sessions plus three-day in-person hackathon (17-19
  June 2026)\n\nMore: https://democracyhackathon.coe.int/
URL:https://democracyhackathon.coe.int/
LOCATION:Palais de l'Europe\, Strasbourg\, France (hybrid: four online warm
 -up sessions leading to a three-day in-person finale)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mozfest-2026-cfp@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260613T225027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260524
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260525
SUMMARY:Deadline: Mozilla Festival (MozFest) 2026: Call for Proposals - Wil
 ding
DESCRIPTION:MozFest 2026 is Mozilla Foundation's annual festival of debates
 \, labs and workshops\, forums\, showcases\, talks and installations - thi
 s year at Recinte Fabra i Coats in Barcelona (28-30 October 2026)\, co-hos
 ted with the City of Barcelona during Open Tech Week. 2026 THEME 'WILDING'
 : a provocation about loosening rigid systems and creating conditions for 
 communities and technologies to evolve collectively\, naturally and intuit
 ively. Inspired by ecological rewilding\, it explores community-owned mesh
  networks\, federated platforms\, open protocols\, community archives\, an
 d tools built on transparency\, trust and mutual flourishing. Mozilla is i
 nviting proposals that exemplify Wilding and celebrate community-led alter
 natives - work that is proof of what is possible. FESTIVAL TRACKS: Wilding
  Advocacy\; Wilding Knowledge\; Wilding Systems\; Wilding With Nature\; Yo
 uth Wilding\; Wilding Creativity\; Founders Wilding\; Developers Wilding. 
 PROCESS: submit a proposal via the MozFest CFP on the Mozilla Foundation f
 estival site\; travel support requests are reviewed after the CFP closes.\
 n\nOrganisation: Mozilla Foundation\nLocation: Barcelona\, Spain (Recinte 
 Fabra i Coats\; co-hosted with the City of Barcelona as part of Open Tech 
 Week)\nAward: Limited travel support\, not guaranteed: flights to Barcelon
 a booked through Mozilla's platform\; a local hotel room reserved by Mozil
 la\; a 5-day Metro pass including airport transfer. No additional funds fo
 r food\, other ground transport or travel insurance. Visa fee reimbursemen
 ts handled through a separate process. NO artist fee\, stipend or honorari
 um.\nDuration: Three days\, 28-30 October 2026\n\nMore: https://www.mozill
 afoundation.org/en/festival/
URL:https://www.mozillafoundation.org/en/festival/
LOCATION:Barcelona\, Spain (Recinte Fabra i Coats\; co-hosted with the City
  of Barcelona as part of Open Tech Week)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ngi-fediversity-11@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260613T225027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Deadline: NGI Fediversity (11th call)
DESCRIPTION:Small to medium-sized R&D grants for projects making federated 
 and self-hosted internet services easier to deploy and operate at scale. F
 unds practical work on portable Fediverse-style infrastructure\, hosted Ma
 stodon-like or PeerTube-like services\, secure email\, private cloud and o
 ther tools that support decentralisation and digital self-determination. O
 pen to individuals and organisations of any type\; results released under 
 free or open-source licences.\n\nOrganisation: NLnet / NGI Fediversity (fu
 nded by EU Horizon Europe)\nLocation: Worldwide\nAward: €5\,000 to €50
 \,000 per project\nDuration: Project-based\n\nMore: https://nlnet.nl/fediv
 ersity/
URL:https://nlnet.nl/fediversity/
LOCATION:Worldwide
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ngi-taler-13@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260613T225027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Deadline: NGI TALER (13th call): Privacy-Preserving Digital Payment
 s
DESCRIPTION:Small to medium-sized R&D grants for free and open source effor
 ts aligned with privacy-preserving digital payments. Build new GNU Taler c
 apabilities\, auxiliary tools\, UX\, FOSS-app and open-standard integratio
 ns (P2P micropayments in messengers\, social media\, video conferencing)\,
  or merchant-backend improvements. All results released under a free or op
 en-source licence. Strong projects can scale up via NGI0 Core.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: NLnet / NGI TALER (with GNU Taler community\, funded by EU Horizon E
 urope and Swiss SERI)\nLocation: Worldwide\nAward: €5\,000 to €50\,000
  per project (€676\,000 total budget for open calls)\nDuration: Project-
 based (programme runs to November 2026)\n\nMore: https://nlnet.nl/taler/
URL:https://nlnet.nl/taler/
LOCATION:Worldwide
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ngi-zero-commons-fund-13@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260613T225027Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Deadline: NGI Zero Commons Fund (13th call)
DESCRIPTION:Small to medium-sized R&D grants to help reclaim the public nat
 ure of the internet across the full technology spectrum: libre silicon\, m
 iddleware\, P2P infrastructure\, end-user applications\, open standards\, 
 open data and AI\, open science\, creative commons and open educational re
 sources. Project results released under free or open-source licences. Aime
 d at troubleshooters tackling hard\, important internet-commons challenges
 . Total programme: €21.6m through 2027.\n\nOrganisation: NLnet / NGI Zer
 o (funded by EU Horizon Europe and Swiss SERI)\nLocation: Worldwide\nAward
 : €5\,000 to €50\,000 per project (scalable for proven potential)\nDur
 ation: Project-based\n\nMore: https://nlnet.nl/commonsfund/
URL:https://nlnet.nl/commonsfund/
LOCATION:Worldwide
END:VEVENT
